Quick documentation on /opt/fgvm/bin
====================================

create-partition  <partition_name> ...
 Create the new partition "partition_name".  Creates a volume group
 if necessary,  copies the whole root volume group from the top level
 into place,  modify printer setup.  Also adds entries into /etc/services
 and /etc/inetd.conf
create-volume-group.pl <volume_group_name> ...
 Interactively creates the volume group(s) given as arguments
delete-partition <partition_name> ...
 Halts "partition_name",  removes its volume groups and removes the
 entries from /etc/services and /etc/inetd.conf 
partition-filesystem-changes.sh <partition_name> ...
 Run as part of create-partition,  this 
partition.fsu <partition_name> ...
partition.isl <partition_name> ...
pcp [ cp args ... ]  partition_name:{directory}
pdevupdate <partition_name> ...
plpsetup <partition_name> ...
pls
pnetconf
pps <partition_name> ...  [ ps args  ... ]
propogate [filename|directory]
pscan <partition_name> ...
pu <partition_name> [cmd]
swpropogate <swpackage>

